{
  "stem": "7458.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we heard trucks coming through the streets, including [POLISH] where we lived, and loudspeakers announcing that all Jews must get dressed, must meet in the center of town near the church once again.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Anybody found not in the center of town after 2 hours would be shot on the spot.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so we knew that liquidation had come.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we had very little time to get dressed or to prepare.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We immediately decided to run into our hiding place above the tannery to see if we could hide.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was probably about 4 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a very cold, wintery long night.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some of my brothers and sisters could not possibly hide, because they had little children.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My brother Meyer had a child.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My sister Mariashe had two children.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my sister Dverke had a little child-- a little boy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They could not hide, because the children would give us away.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they had no choice, with many others, to march off into town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My sister Dverke, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] who was very emotional, she grabbed her child, her baby, and ran into the garden where the well was.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she jumped into the well with her child in her arms.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Those of us who could, including my father, my mother, my brothers, my brother Maishe, my other sisters, and some of the other people who were not members of our family but who lived in our house, we all ended up crawling up to the crawlspace to the hiding place above the tannery.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I don't know if perhaps this might be good idea to show you or to describe how this hiding place worked.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
